activities.name: Informed consent
activities.description: Obtain written informed consent from participant

activities.name: Admit to unit
activities.description: Participants will be admitted to the clinical research unit (CRU)

activities.name: Discharge from unit
activities.description: Discharge from the unit may occur after completion of all procedures on Day 9 and on Day 40

activities.name: Outpatient visit or phone call
activities.description: A single outpatient visit or phone call and safety laboratory assessment should occur between Day 14 and Day 18

activities.name: Inclusion/exclusion
activities.description: Review of inclusion and exclusion criteria

activities.name: HIV, hepatitis B and C screen
Medical history/demographics
activities.description: Parameters include age and sex. Race and ethnicity will be collected where permitted

activities.name: WD history
activities.description: Wilson disease history including diagnosis date and method

activities.name: Prior WD treatment
activities.description: Details of previous Wilson disease treatments

activities.name: Physical examination
activities.description: A full physical examination will be performed at Screening, check-in, and EOS

activities.name: Blood sampling for PK: Plasma total Mo and PUF-Mo
PD: Plasma total and PUF-Cu, LBC, ceruloplasmin, ceruloplasmin-bound Cu
Urine/serum pregnancy test
activities.description: Pregnancy testing for females of childbearing potential

activities.name: Retained serum sample (safety)
activities.description: A single 15 mL serum sample will be retained

activities.name: Vitals sign measurements
activities.description: Body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and blood pressure

activities.name: Adverse events
activities.description: Monitoring and recording of adverse events

activities.name: Cu/Mo-controlled meals
activities.description: Initiation and maintenance of controlled diet

activities.name: Urination and bowel movement monitoring, menstruation check
